// Classic Codeforces-style problem.
// Given array of n POSITIVE integers and integer s,
// find the length of the smallest contiguous subarray
// whose sum >= s. If none exists, output 0.
// Constraints: n <= 2e5, elements in [1, 1e4], s <= 1e9
// Example: arr = [2,3,1,2,4,3], s = 7 → answer = 2 (subarray [4,3])

